DataElement.preferredName: Subject Activity Group Reuse Template Study Activity Repeat Frequency Ratio ISO21090.RTO.INT,PQ.TIME.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A collection of activities from a global library that would be performed on a common subject at approximately the same time. EXAMPLE(S): Clinic visit during which a physical exam, a blood test, and a substance administration occur. Telephone contact during which temperature, blood pressure and adverse events are reported. Recording multiple observation results in a diary. A ratio representing the number of occurrences of an activity within a given time period. EXAMPLE(S): Once per 12 hours; 2 times per day
